Login to minikube in gitbash

ssh -i <keypair> centos@<IP>
mkdir .kube
cp kubeconfig .kube/config
kubectl get nodes
cd .kube/config
cat config




Workstation/client server
To check the docker isntallation logs
sudo tail -f /var/log/cloud-init-output.log

Install kubectl client 
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl
kubectl version --client


To connect to the kubernetes cluster we need authentication.
mkdir .kube
sudo vim .kube/config 
paste the kubernetes authentication file. Check the 8th line.
kubectl get nodes

